"reviewcomment":"Sure it&#39;s in a touristy area, but still popular with locals; people were lined up for tables early by European standards for dinner. You walk by a very tempting spread of antipasti by the door, but save room, because the main dishes and even the entrees are the most generous portions I&#39;ve had in France. A salad can fill you up, and was laden with artichokes and cheese. Three of us split the spaghetti fruits de mer, which came out on a heavy platter three times the size of my face! It was heavy with mussels, calimari, clams, and crevette, and I couldn&#39;t believe it was just 18 euros.<br><br>We all ate well, and had some local rose, for just 19 euros each. Don&#39;t let the location or plastic patio put you off, this was my favorite meal in Nice!",
