"reviewcomment":"Good food and good service and isn&#39;t that what you want in a restaurant?<br><br>We stopped in with a pretty large group on a Wednesday night.  Since they were expecting us- we had the entire room to ourselves .<br><br>We started with a few &#34;family style&#34; appetizers- a wonderful charcuterie plate loaded with meats, sun dried tomatoes, mushrooms and artichokes.  The other plate was an assortment of ratatouille , deep fried squash blossoms,  and other tasty treats.  Everything was fresh and delicious!<br><br>I had the swordfish and vegetables for my entree and others had the veal and spaghetti.  Both were large portions and very good.  The veal actually came out in the pan it was cooked in adding to the overall ambiance.<br><br>Our server kept our wine glasses full and was very good about replenishing the water.<br><br>All in all a very nice place to have a delicious meal!",
