"ogimage":"http://s3-media4.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/dCI8UGks1gJ4qJE3l-vxrw/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"This place has the best salade nicoise I&#39;ve ever had.  I keep trying to find a similar version at other restaurants that serve it, but so far no luck.  It is one of those rare and remarkable foods you remember years after having eaten it.  It is sheer perfection, from the high quality canned tuna, to the chiffonade of basil, to the clear glass bowl it&#39;s served in.  Using canned tuna makes a huge difference in flavor.  Fresh tuna tastes completely different, and cannot stand up to the strong flavors of the other ingredients of this salad. The basil is a key ingredient of this version of salade nicoise.  It elevates this salad to a whole new level.  And the the large clear bowl makes the salad easy to toss and to find the particular morsels you want.<br><br>The zucchini blossoms are to die for.  Like gossamers of petals that melt instantly in your mouth.  So delicate and so subtle in flavor.  Simply exquisite.<br><br>The truffle pasta, the langostino, the perfectly seared scallops -- all are delicious.  My only wish is that they open a restaurant in San Diego.  And it would be helpful if the prices were lower too.",
