"reviewcomment":"The food is delicious. I had the truffle risotto, which I strongly recommend. As expected of anything with truffle, it was really rich, but not overly so. The risotto was quite creamy and both the flavor and texture were perfect. It was sprinkled with a bit of fresh chives on top which very subtly adds to the look and taste. The portions here are not very big; enough to fill you up, but you might want an appetizer if you&#39;re really hungry. Their duck steak is also really good. It&#39;s juicy and very tender and easy to chew. They don&#39;t seem to marinate or season it much with anything, and the meat itself is just of high quality and taste. The tartare is also quite good if you&#39;re into raw meat.<br><br>When I ate here, instead of giving you small menus like any other restaurant, our waiter came up with a chalkboard that had the day&#39;s menu written out on it. He explained the menu along with the specials and gave some recommendations. He was very knowledgable. It was a very unique experience that I think adds to the quaintness and charm of the place.<br><br>The waiters were all really friendly and spoke English very well. Service was fairly quick. The price is fair. I wish I could give a more detailed review, but it has been over a month since I was here; I couldn&#39;t remember the restaurant until now, but I do remember that I absolutely loved everything about this place. Definitely eat here if you&#39;re in Nice!",
