"reviewcomment":"17 Euros for a 3 course lunch. Enuf said. Jk. <br><br>I didn&#39;t understand that I was supposed to choose one starter, main and a dessert. So I ordered 3 starters for myself and my hubby. The waiter looked a little startled but maintained his composure and placed my order. <br><br>The lentils with mussels was amazing. I am not a fan of lentils, but Chez Palmyre&#39;s lentils were amazing. They were probably Puy lentils. The mussels were fresh. It was my favorite thing on the menu. <br><br>The croque monsier was good as well, but not special. <br><br>Veggie soup (soup du jur) was decent. It was a little bland, we should have salted but didn&#39;t. Our error. <br><br>Veal main dish was good. Again it could have used a little salt but I didn&#39;t salt. Our error again. <br><br>Hubby ordered the gnocchi. Don&#39;t worry I gave him grief for this lack of judgement. He said he didn&#39;t want any meat. Whatevers. It was not good, it was not bad. I&#39;ve had worse gnocchi. <br><br>We skipped dessert because we were stuffed.  Looked at the bill and was amazed at the quality that we got for the price. <br><br>Even though I didn&#39;t love more than half my dishes, for the price, it can&#39;t be beat.",
