"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"Our first meal in Nice after a train ride down from Paris earlier that day. To start My husband had the soft egg with mushrooms and asparagus (delicious!) and I had the Ceasar salad with prosciutto which was good too. For dinner he ordered the duck with shrimps and vegetables, which must have been pretty good as he wouldn&#39;t share much with me. It featured two pieces of duck breast, seared with the skin on and two large prawns shelled, but with their heads still attached. The somolier recommended either a red for the duck or a white for the prawns, so my husband went with the Pinot Noir as it was light enough to go with both--good choice. <br><br>For dessert we shared an apple tart with a light caramel sauce. Very good!<br><br>The restaurant has chalk written menus in both French and English and they speak English very well--which was helpful for us. The clientele that evening was mostly English speaking, but that may have been a random event as it didn&#39;t appear to be touristy at all. <br><br>The decor was lovely and the tables arrangements were fun as they had two sets of bench-style seating in the center of the restaurant. We were seated at one end of a bench, another couple at the other, and about half-way through dinner service a new couple arrived and we had to get up to let them in.",
