"rating":"2.5",
"reviewcomment":"Giuseppe and Pepino it is the new restaurant / ice-cream maker who has just settled down on the place Garibaldi.<br><br> Nice, rather young and cool decoration.<br><br> Concerning the restaurant:<br>Great to come to eat, a lot of people here as soon as the sun turns up tables are installed on the place garibaldi and take advantage of the sun. It is very pleasant to come to eat here, and many persons understood it because it is necessary to wait to have its table.<br>We find here many Italian dishes with a good value for money : salads, pastas (very substantial dishes), spread (big slice of grilled bread furnished in the choice)...<br><br> Disappointed by a dish: Italian sandwiches (bread burned out with mozzarella, tomatoes, cured ham). The mozzarella was in grain (down-market type for pizza) mixed in some good mozzarella (di buffala) and just dissolve on the top (not below) what was not really good.<br>Roughly as soon as I lifted a little the dissolve(fade out) of the top I met with heights of mini-quadrate of mozzarella not swept down on the bottom... Really not too much to mix low and high-end and besides the same good step to melt the cheese...<br><br> I appreciate quite particularly the Sunday opening, that will allow me to go there a little more often.<br><br> Concerning ice creams: if we listen to the waitress, here ice creams are made without colouring agents...<br><br> By looking at the smarties ice cream that is fluorescent blue, and by eating it (yuk for my part) and by finding me with blue tongue like a stroumpf at the end of two minutes, I admit to have severe doubts on this point!<br><br> The waitress explained to us that the mixture of smarties all together gives this color to the ice cream. <br>Anyway in smarties there are colouring agents and so the ice cream contains it necessarily!<br>I was also able to enjoy the ice cream tiramisu, that I don&#39;t like, I found the taste not really natural...<br><br> Feel reassured Fenocchio, you always remain the best ice-cream maker of Nice!",
