"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"During my stay in Nice Adonis was the first restaurant I visited and I have to say that I came out of there really impressed! (it is rare for me to give 5 stars to an establishment)<br><br> Everyone is friendly there, there isn&#39;t such thing as a stereotypical French waiter, and they speak different languages. As I am not a connoisseur of Lebanese food they helped me out with an assorted plate of several different things and I really enjoyed it, they were fast serving me! Which also counts as a bonus!<br>As desserts are related I only have to say, try the Baklawa! Very very good!<br><br> The architecture of the place is very minimal, they have a large counter with their national desserts/sweets and several tables, at a Friday lunchtime the place was comfortably full! From the outside it really doesn&#39;t look like a Lebanese restaurant, it suggests some sort of Greek origins, it is situated in the street that leads to the Cours Saleya.<br><br> This is a worthy restaurant to visit when you are in Nice!",
