"rating":"2.5",
"reviewcomment":"I can&#39;t believe I am even writing a review for this restaurant. Chez Juliette is one of those once in a lifetime romantic eating experiences that you just don&#39;t want to share with other people. From the outside, it looks like you&#39;re in Provence dining in someones sunny yellow hued charming farmhouse restaurant. The food did not disappoint either. <br><br>Roasted foie gras with fig on toast was to die for and their veal steak was the best veal I&#39;ve ever had in my life. If there&#39;s one thing the French do great, it&#39;s meat. The quality of their meat is significantly higher and you can taste it. The veal was thin and just perfectly cooked. Juicy and tender. <br><br>There are so many great restaurants in this town that you could probably walk in anywhere and have a fantastic experience. Come here, bring a loved one, have a glass of wine and truly drift off to French paradise.",
