"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"Such a lovely hole-in-the-wall restaurant. Just a warning - it&#39;s a little difficult to get to and you have to drive narrow mountain roads. Also, there&#39;s no real parking, you just park on the side of the narrow street (and be careful of rushing/oncoming cars). <br><br>I made a reservation the day before through e-mail (which is a good idea to do as the place fills up). The staff got back to me within the hour and were very accommodating.<br><br>We ended up on this place because it was Michelin recommended. I&#39;d read some online forums with good things to say so I decided to try out  &#34;Provençal Cuisine.&#34; The menu does come in an Italian/English version if you ask. The prix fixe menu deals are a great value, especially because it&#39;s France. <br><br>We had a wonderful meal; the foie gras was very good and the steak was cooked nicely. My boyfriend and I each received a huge portion for our steak - cooked medium. It came with a sort of potato mash and stewed vegetables (Ratatouille) which were delicious. Everything had a very home-made feel. For dessert I ended up getting coffee glace (ice cream) and lemon sorbet - mmmm delicious.  Great value and great food. <br><br>I also loved the cute kitty that greets you at the front door. This was a wonderful experience and definitely somewhere I&#39;ll continue recommending to people who&#39;ll be visiting the area.",
