"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/czjUGb0XhMnOw0Kr8_Xu2A/l.jpg",
"rating":"3.5",
"reviewcomment":"It was easy getting a dinner reservation because it was the night of Nice&#39;s Festival of the Port. The maitre d&#39; was extremely welcoming and gracious from the moment we walked in. We requested a table outside so we could enjoy the perfect weather. <br><br>We were served a variety of fresh baked breads. Our favorite was the bread with olives baked inside. The bread was moist and olives added an extra zing. We were also served two very different amuse bouche. We appreciated the details that must&#39;ve gone into creating such delicate tastes. We finally settled on the gazpacho which was refreshing and flavorful. For our next course we ordered the sea bass. The white meat of the fish was soft and flaky. The skin was crispy and salty adding extra flavor. For dessert we had a delicious apertif to compliment our pistachio tapioca with foam on top. We were stuffed but couldn&#39;t stop eating the tapicoa. It was so smooth and cool. The foam on top not only provided an interesting texture, but was extremely light and delicious. <br><br>The best part of our evening was when we got to meet the head chef. He had been representing his restaurant at the Festival and had just come back. I asked him for an autograph. He was very gracious and wrote a beautiful note in French. I will always remember my perfect evening at L&#39;Ane Rouge.",
