"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/assets/2/www/img/76df14aad260/default_avatars/business_large_square.png",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"So, the newly renamed Missus Paradise and I found this place among the alley ways and side streets behind the flower market in Nice last week.  Intent on finding a nice spot to have some wine and cheese on our day in this interesting French town.<br><br>The interior was decorated with a hodge podge of different items, various cool pictures, a giant movie poster of &#34;Chat Noir, Chat Blanc.&#34;  (not entirely familiar with the film)  and other assorted paintings which we were told from the owner, a tall, dreadlocked French fellow (reggae played in the background) he decorated himself.  <br><br>He was quite friendly to two tourists that could barely speak the language and brought us out a complementary bruschetta type dish to accompany our fromagé and wine.  The various cheeses were really good and I have to say, and I bet this sounds a little dumb, (but anyhow) the sliced French bread was probably some of the best I&#39;ve ever had.<br><br>We didn&#39;t stay long, but in the little time we spent there, friends of the owner came by to say hello and chat for a bit.  Seemed like place that the locals enjoy.  <br><br>The kicker for me, what sold me was simple.  On a small wooden shelf above the main counter they had all their liquor bottles.  In the center of  the shelf, what sat there but a big bottle of Duff Beer.   International, yeah.<br><br>Great find.  Look for it if you find yourself here.",
