"rating":"3.0",
"reviewcomment":"The Foundouk is conveniently located on Place Garibaldi, walking distance from the port, the shopping area of Massena and the old town. It has outdoor seating and a nicely decorated interior. When you step in you truly feel you instantly flew into Casablanca. <br>So the decor is nice, the service is perfect but the food is what will keep you coming back. The place has a decent a la carte menu that includes traditional appetizers: hummus, eggplant caviar, lentil soups...and an array of couscous and tagines. It also offers a prix fixe option of 28 or 29 euros that gives you a choice of appetizer, a choice of couscous or tagines and a fresh orange salad for dessert.<br>This is France so alcohol is also served with an excellent choice of cocktails, Moroccan wines or local French wines.<br>The highlights: the tagine with lamb and prunes was outstanding: meat melting in the mouth and nice balance of cinnamon, prune and spices. I would go back just for that.<br>Don&#39;t forget to end your meal with mint tea, also well prepared and served the traditional way.<br>Overall, a really good Moroccan restaurant that merits our business.",
