"reviewcomment":"Finally after many mediocre meals in touristy old town a really excellent meal. This was my top meal while visiting Nice, one of my top meals I&#39;ve ever had actually. <br><br>Started with escargot and faux gras. Two different types of escargot and both were truly delicious. The faux gras was so silky smooth and melted in your mouth. Best faux gras I&#39;ve had yet. <br><br>For main course I had thin sliced beef over a bed of fresh local veggies and salad with chunks of parmesan. All was amazing. My sister had stake tartare, normally I am not a fan of this but her was very tasty and I couldn&#39;t help asking for more and more. <br><br>For desert I had a chocolate cake with vanilla ice cream on top and a melted chocolate center. Super good! My mom got a apple crumble with caramel salt ice cream. The apple crumble wasn&#39;t anything to write home about but the caramel salt ice cream was simply amazing. <br><br>If you&#39;re looking for good food away from tourist central come here and you won&#39;t be disappointed!",
