"reviewcomment":"I had lunch here during a weekend in Nice.  While everything on the menu looked delicious, I ended up going with a &#34;fruits de mer&#34; pizza.  I wasn&#39;t disappointed.  It was a traditional rustic flatbread pizza, asymmetrical, with a layer of tangy tomato sauce, topped with bits of saute&#39;ed fish, scallops, crab, and squid, as well as a generous helping of mozzerella cheese.  For about 14 EUR it was a bit pricey, but all in all the meal was large and filling, and realistically I was paying for the gorgeous view of the Mediterranean as well.  Plus, I got out of the hot sun and into the shade of the canopy, where they have little misty sprayers to keep us tourists cool.<br><br>Anyway, I&#39;d definitely check this place out again!",
