"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"I went to this place tonight based on Sue P&#39;s review. I must say it is a great find in Nice! The food was excellent &amp; quite reasonably priced. It is a family-run business &amp; they are nice people with fair English skills. I loved the pelimini pasta dish ad the pork ribs (not BBQ sauce, it was seasoned with herbs), which was served with a good-sized portion of fries and salad. The location is off the beaten path, a few blocks away from all of the hullaballoo, but really a true gem. You can actually have a conversation with others in your party here without having to yell over other clients and street noise. I will definitely be back &amp; make this one of my regular stops when I&#39;m in the south of France. Another important thing to note is that it is on a side street of Blvd Victor Hugo and not on the main boulevard itself. If you actually go to &#34;2 Blvd Victor Hugo&#34; rather than &#34;2 Passage Victor Hugo,&#34; you will end up in front of the BNP Paribas bank. The location of the restaurant is actually one block south (towards the water &amp; action) from there. Check this place out if you are in town. If you go on-line and look at the reviews of this place in French (there are several on other websites), they are also mostly quite good.",
