"ogimage":"http://s3-media3.ak.yelpcdn.com/assets/2/www/img/76df14aad260/default_avatars/business_large_square.png",
"rating":"5.0",
"reviewcomment":"On our first day in Nice, the hotel suggested to walk and choose a restaurante onon rue Massena (which is the main pedestrian street on the modern part of town) but the restaurantes on this street were not appeling since they were mainly kebab and pizzas or what looked like tourist traps. So we went to a small side street were we found this tiny restaurante (total they can sit 12 or 13 people.   The owners are a wife (server) and husband (chef)were super accomodating, especially with our twin babies.  the food was traditional French, I had a steak and my wife has chicken.  They were not creative dishes but everything was excellent.  My steak had a very light pepper sauce and my wife chicken was moist and tender.  The best on the plate was the side vegtables that were to die for... And lastly we shared a chocolate cake the last day and this was really something awesome.  IT was like a brownie with awesome choclate sauce covering it...  Coming from late eats in Spain we were the last to leave the restaurante and the owners held the babies when they got fussy and really enjoyed talking to us.  Just a great experience and it came relatively cheap since we spent less than €36 euros for both of us.  <br><br>Wish we could have found some more of these places on our trip to nice.",
