"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I stumbled into this cute little place desperately in need of some lunch.  The owner, Fernando (sp?) warmly welcomed me and handed me a menu.<br><br>Now not knowing what to expect, I thought this was a coffee shop- but instead I found myself in a little place that serves breakfast, lunch, and early dinner ( they close at 19:00) and they specialize in Italian food and vegetarian cuisine. They promote themselves as a cafe, a salon de the, and a restaurant. ( forgive my spelling but my computer doesn&#39;t seem to have any of the right accent marks to spell the French properly!)<br><br>On the day I was there- the plat du jour was a mushroom lasagna (delicious!) which was a huge portion for the money.  I also had the Italian salad which was also quite large and came with mixed greens, buffalo mozzarella, ham, sun dried tomatoes and egg.  Good thing I had brought along a friend so that we could split these two items.  Add in a glass of wine for me and a latte for him and we were very happy with our choices.<br><br>The place is simple but brightened up immensely when brightly colored placemats and napkins were set down before me.  And I loved the large glass that my wine was served in!<br><br>And the even better news?  Lunch for two including drinks was only about 25e.<br><br>My French is not good but Fernando was so accommodating he made me feel like I was a guest in his home.  We even exchanged some pleasantries about where I was from in the States and about his home in Italy.  It&#39;s one of the things I love about travel- just getting to know about other people and places in the world.<br><br>If you find yourself in Nice- check out this little gem.  I almost passed it by. . . . .but you won&#39;t want to!",
