"ogimage":"http://s3-media1.ak.yelpcdn.com/bphoto/ihZHp778a8RbSc4NdFGL2g/l.jpg",
"rating":"4.0",
"reviewcomment":"I went to go to another restaurant I had read about, but it was closed, so I was wandering around the area that appeared to be the equivalent of Nice&#39;s Chinatown.  There were several restaurants, but this very small, narrow restaurant had a lot of people and they were almost all Asian.  I went in.  It&#39;s proven to be a good indicator of the quality of the food in such neighborhoods.  I never go by appearance in this situation.<br><br>It&#39;s only narrow enough for two rows of tables and one aisle down the middle.  A few girls were singing Chinese karaoke in the back, and a very friendly, smiling woman brought me the menu and took my order.  When I ordered the roast duck, she asked me a question (we were speaking French) with a word I didn&#39;t know.  We had to enlist the help of some students from Beijing who actually spoke English better than French and they said she was asking if I wanted my duck to have bones or not.  I said I didn&#39;t care, and it came without.  It was nice without, actually.<br><br>The duck was moist and tasty and I got just white rice with it.",
